Hundreds of young people participated to create innovative smart mobility applications, utilising both Gauteng Freeway Improvement Project toll gantry data and WhereIsMyTransport public transport related data. Sanral region manager Randall Cable said it is encouraging to see how committed young South Africans are to change. Zikhona Nqula and her group of four: Damian Beukes, Sabatha Poncama, and Zimvo Matwa said their idea was to create an App for the disabled, which is "more like Uber/Taxify App", but specifically for disabled people. Melany Kühn, senior consultant said: “Among the participants, the winning team will walk away with a R20000 and a year's worth of free access to the WhereIsMyTransport.” To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video @SISONKE_MD  sisonke.mlamla@inl.co.za  Cape Argus